\
10. President Trump made misleading statements about the Ukraine war and his relationship with Vladimir Putin, including claims of ending multiple wars (2025-08-18): Downplaying Russian aggression and exaggerating his peacemaking role muddied public understanding of the conflict and U.S. commitments to democratic allies.\
\
11. Winnie Greco, former adviser to New York Mayor Eric Adams gave a reporter cash hidden in a potato chip bag at a campaign event (2025-08-20): Offering concealed cash to a journalist at a political event raised concerns about attempts to influence coverage and blurred ethical lines between campaigns and the press.\
\
12. Federal Communications Commission and Senator Adam Schiff faced a request to investigate whether Trump sought programming commitments in exchange for approving a major media merger (2025-08-18): Allegations that merger approval might have been tied to favorable coverage highlighted risks that regulatory decisions could be traded for media loyalty, threatening editorial independence.\
\
13. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention announced a new survey program (HTOPS) including questions on attitudes toward the 2030 Census (2025-08-20): Collecting high-frequency data on household trends and census attitudes aimed to improve understanding of public views, informing future outreach and planning for a core democratic count.\
